.\" termin.al-name: less
.\" termin.al-usage: less <path>
.\" termin.al-summary: Open raw virtual document text in a pager.
.TH LESS 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
less \- Open raw virtual document text in a pager.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
less <path>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens one virtual document in termin.al's raw pager. The pager keeps GNU-less-like presentation separate from the Vim manpage viewer.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ less notes/sample-note.md
.fi
.SH NOTES
Keys include j/k and the arrow keys, PageUp/b, PageDown/Space, g/G, Ctrl+f and q/Escape. Ctrl+b remains the pane-prefix key.
.SH SEE ALSO
man(1), cat(1)
